Problem Statement

Develop a Java application to demonstrate method overriding using inheritance. Create a parent class named Animal with a method called sound(). Derive the classes Dog, Cat, and Cow from the Animal 
class and override the sound() method in each class to display their respective sounds.

package Raghul;

import java.util.*;

class Animal {

    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Animal makes a sound");
    }

}

class Dog extends Animal {

    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Dog Sound : Bark");
    }

}

class Cat extends Animal {

    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Cat Sound : Meow");
    }

}

class Cow extends Animal {

    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Cow Sound : Moo");
    }

}

public class AnimalSoundSystem {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Dog d = new Dog();
        Cat c = new Cat();
        Cow cw = new Cow();

        d.sound();
        c.sound();
        cw.sound();

    }
}
Output
Dog Sound : Bark
Cat Sound : Meow
Cow Sound : Moo
